#: Game.Levels.GroupWorld.L06_RightIdentity
msgid "Now, the second half of the pair. And with it, a new tactic! If we have a lemma in the form of a logical implication (§0), and our goal is §1, then we know that if §2 holds, our goal must also hold. This means that we can just prove §3 instead. §4 will replace the goal in the form of §5's conclusion §6 with its hypothesis §7. We can also §8 where §9 is §10 to turn it into §11. Using this, we must prove that the left identity §12 also serves as a right identity."
